Input:
    Substrate atomic coordinates r_i
    Effective total correlation function h(r)
    Spatial domain Ω(x,z)
    Mesh resolution Nx × Nz

Output:
    Interfacial density map Δρ(x,z)

1: Construct graphite substrate using ABAB-stacked graphene layers
2: Define substrate atom coordinates r_i = (x_i, y_i, z_i)
3: Generate a uniform Nx × Nz mesh over Ω(x,z)
4:
5: for each mesh point R = (x,0,z) do
6:     Initialize local density contribution:
7:         Δρ(R) ← 0
8:
9:     for each substrate atom r_i do
10:         Compute distance:
11:             d_i ← |R − r_i|
12:
13:         Evaluate ETCF contribution:
14:             Δρ(R) ← Δρ(R) + h(d_i)
15:     end for
16: end for
17:
18: Apply short-range cutoff corrections:
19:     h(r < 0.18 nm) ← −50
20:     h(r < 0.07 nm) ← NaN
21:
22: Reshape Δρ(R) into a two-dimensional density map
23: Visualize Δρ(x,z) using a customized colormap
24:
25: return Δρ(x,z)
